(2673,'3EB01073725B6D0037055F','231335629164614@lid',NULL,'Curtis','61466848838:16@s.whatsapp.net','Me',1,'I\'m in conversation with Gemini, the same conversation window as the deep research and i\'ve asked it for name suggestions, 1 word, no odd spelling and not taken in market: 1. Vanza\nThe Vibe: Punchy, modern, and energetic.\n\nWhy it works: It subtly evokes the word \"Van\" (perfect for mobile detailers, mobile dog groomers, or field techs) without explicitly locking you into the automotive industry. It sounds like a tool that drives momentum.\n\n2. Rovera\nThe Vibe: Friendly, reliable, and approachable.\n\nWhy it works: \"Roving\" means traveling constantly without a fixed destination. It perfectly describes a mobile service business. Plus, if you eventually expand into the pet care niche, \"Rover\" is an incredible crossover keyword.\n\n3. Arivo\nThe Vibe: Professional, sleek, and results-oriented.\n\nWhy it works: A play on the word \"Arrive.\" The entire goal of your dispatch and scheduling module is to help the sole trader arrive on time, look professional, and get paid.\n\n4. Routis (Pronounced Route-iss)\nThe Vibe: Tech-forward and highly operational.\n\nWhy it works: It combines \"Route\" with the feeling of an \"OS\" (Operating System). It tells the user immediately that this is the software that manages their path for the day, regardless of what industry they are in.',NULL,'conversation',1778221831,'2026-05-08 06:30:31',NULL,NULL,NULL),
