(2863,'3EB070E93F9336C4988B87','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Curtis','61466848838:16@s.whatsapp.net','Me',1,'I\'m curious, there are a number of sections where claude has said it should be connected to a 3rd party to manage aspects of the software. Are you saying Forgebox can actually manage them all? E.g. I had it build out a very thorough PRD and am mostly finished all the build phases, but throughout the processes it wanted accounts for the following so it could wire it up fully for release later:  1. Clerk — auth\n  2. Neon — Postgres\n  3. Vercel — hosting + Blob storage + Cron\n  * 4. GitHub — repo / CI source\n  * 5. Stripe (Billing) — SaaS subscription\n  * 6. Stripe Connect — operator payouts (1% platform fee)\n  * 7. Xero — accounting sync of paid invoices\n  8. Resend — transactional email + daily reminder cron\n  9. OpenStreetMap Nominatim — address autocomplete',NULL,'conversation',1778363323,'2026-05-09 21:48:43',NULL,NULL,NULL),
