(2916,'3EB0B47C1E9FD3F4D40DCC','231335629164614@lid',NULL,'Regan','231335629164614@lid','Regan',0,'Reverse DNS (PTR records) cannot be set through Cloudflare. PTR records are managed by the ISP that owns the IP address — in this case, Aussie Broadband (AS4764), who owns the 61.245.155.x block.\n\nYou\'ll need to contact Aussie Broadband support and request they set the reverse DNS for 61.245.155.95 to mail.vanza.rm-hq.net.',NULL,'extendedTextMessage',1778379136,'2026-05-10 02:12:16',NULL,NULL,NULL),
(2917,'3EB0200AFDD83DE4444617','231335629164614@lid',NULL,'Regan','231335629164614@lid','Regan',0,'Done! A record created:\n\nmail.vanza.rm-hq.net → 61.245.155.95 (DNS only, no proxy)\nThis is set to DNS only (grey cloud) since it\'s for mail — mail servers typically need direct DNS resolution without Cloudflare proxying.\n\nNow when you contact Aussie Broadband to set the reverse DNS for 61.245.155.95 → mail.vanza.rm-hq.net, the forward-confirmed reverse DNS will be complete:\n\nForward: mail.vanza.rm-hq.net → 61.245.155.95 ✅\nReverse: 61.245.155.95 → mail.vanza.rm-hq.net ⏳ (pending Aussie Broadband setup)',NULL,'extendedTextMessage',1778379181,'2026-05-10 02:13:02',NULL,NULL,NULL),
