(3333,'3EB0CF95A3C2A04008D057','120363400908812783@g.us',NULL,'Curtis','61466848838:16@s.whatsapp.net','Me',1,'Do you mind having a read through this version. Maybe get toby to as well and see if he agrees, before i send it back:\n\nHi Kayleen,\n\nThank you for sending this through. I did a side-by-side read of the 1.06 and 1.07 drafts against the points you raised.\n\nMy current read is as follows:\n\n\n\n\n\nWarranties\nI may be missing something, but I do not see clause 14.1 as having been materially narrowed between these two drafts. In both versions, clause 14 appears to include the same core warranties: 180-day deliverables conformity, authority/compliance with applicable laws, SaaS conformity/no malicious code, no material degradation, and privacy/data protection compliance.\n\n\n\nACL safe harbour\nI was not able to verify this as a change between 1.06 and 1.07. Both versions appear to end the warranties section with the same disclaimer language, but I could not identify an express ACL/non-excludable guarantees carve-out in either of the two drafts I reviewed.\n\n\n\nAnti-corruption / modern slavery\nI could not locate those provisions in either of the two drafts I reviewed, so I was not able to confirm that they were removed in 1.07.\n\n\n\nInsurance\nSimilarly, I could not locate the public liability / professional indemnity / cyber liability wording in either draft, so I was not able to verify a deletion between these two versions.\n\n\n\nIndemnity caps\nOn my read, this point does not seem to be borne out by the 1.06 vs 1.07 comparison. In both versions, all indemnities under clause 16 are made subject to clause 17, with a specific indemnity cap of AUD 300,000, and only fraud or wilful misconduct carved out from the caps.\n\n\n\nCompliance clause / Supplier Code of Conduct\nI could not locate the Supplier Code of Conduct / Standards of Business Conduct wording in either of the two drafts I reviewed, so I was not able to verify that as a change between these versions.\n\n\n\nTerm\nThe point on the 3-year structure and stale commencement date still looked directionally right on my read, although I have not independently traced that against any version earlier than 1.06/1.07.\n\n\n\nIP / business continuity\nI do share the concern that the contract text does not obviously reflect the perpetual royalty-free internal deployment position described in Kelly’s email. On the face of the agreement, the operative licence wording appears narrower than that.\n\n\n\nUptime\nI agree this is a genuine improvement in 1.07. It introduces a 99.0% monthly uptime target, allows News Corp to log unavailability outside Scheduled Maintenance as a Severity 1 incident, and provides for a quarterly uptime summary on request. That said, I did not see a termination trigger for persistent failure, and the reporting commitment appears to be quarterly rather than monthly.\n\nOverall, my current read is that the clearest changes supported by the 1.06/1.07 comparison are the uptime improvements, with a possible separate issue around whether the licence/business continuity position is fully reflected in the operative drafting. Several of the other points may depend on an earlier draft rather than the specific 1.06 and 1.07 versions I reviewed.\n\nIf I am looking at the wrong mark-up or missing a schedule, I am very happy to revisit.',NULL,'conversation',1778589149,'2026-05-12 12:32:30',NULL,NULL,NULL),
