(3365,'3EB0A1AE1ACD4F765E7D53','120363400908812783@g.us',NULL,'Dwayne Baird','144221143048242@lid','Dwayne Baird',0,'Updates in, I have changed the Insurance with the following notes:\n\nInserted in v1.08 in response to the insurance requirements raised. We\'ve added a right-sized insurance clause rather than the schedule originally proposed, for the following reasons:\n\n(1) Public Liability has been omitted because the Services are delivered remotely with no on-site work, no physical goods, and no third-party physical exposure that PL is designed to cover. \n\n(2) Professional Indemnity at $1M aligns with the Aggregate Cap in clause 17.1 (twelve months\' fees, which is at most a fraction of the build fee given the SaaS is provided at no ongoing charge). $5M PI is disproportionate to the contractual liability ceiling and would represent unfunded overhead on the engagement.\n\n(3) Cyber Liability at $1M reflects the pseudonymisation architecture. The Platform holds only opaque identifiers linked to assessment and succession data, and PI is ultimately contained on the side of Workday with their own liabilities. Breach exposure is bounded compared with a typical SaaS holding identifiable customer records.\n\nThe 12-month tail has been reduced to 6 months to align with the Aggregate Cap period in clause 17.1 and to reduce the unfunded run-off cost.\n\nHappy to discuss limits, structure, or any of the underlying reasoning. If different limits are required.',NULL,'conversation',1778635818,'2026-05-13 01:30:18',NULL,NULL,NULL),
