(3482,'3EB07C083CE11617D49B12','231335629164614@lid',NULL,'Curtis','61466848838:16@s.whatsapp.net','Me',1,'In the left sidebar under Advanced Settings → LAN → tab DHCP Server:\n\n  1. Scroll down to Manually Assigned IP around the DHCP list\n  2. Set Enable Manual Assignment to Yes\n  3. Click Add Manual Assignment (or the + button)\n  4. From the MAC Address dropdown, find forgebox-d4118f (the Pi\'s hostname). If it\'s not in the dropdown, you can type the MAC manually — Pi\'s wlan0 MAC.\n  5. Set IP address to 192.168.50.122\n  6. Apply at the bottom\n\n  3. Port forward TCP 587\n\n  In the left sidebar → Advanced Settings → WAN → tab Virtual Server / Port Forwarding:\n\n  1. Enable Port Forwarding: switch to Yes\n  2. Click Add Profile (or + Add new rule)\n  3. Fill in:\n\n  | Field         | Value                                                                        |\n  |---------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n  | Service Name  | Postfix submission (or Vanza SMTP)                                           |\n  | Protocol      | TCP                                                                          |\n  | External Port | 587                                                                          |\n  | Internal IP   | 192.168.50.122 (or pick from the connected-clients list — should be your Pi) |\n  | Internal Port | 587                                                                          |\n  | Source IP     | leave blank                                                                  |\n\n  4. OK / Apply\n  5. The rule should appear in the list. Click Apply at the bottom of the page to commit.',NULL,'extendedTextMessage',1778672711,'2026-05-13 11:45:11',NULL,NULL,NULL),
