(3607,'3EB09A4AB12F6D686BCACA','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Regan','231335629164614@lid','Regan',0,'## Built-in Tyro Integration (Direct Integration)\n\nSome POS systems integrate directly with Tyro\'s own SDK/API, cutting out Linkly entirely. It\'s simpler and has fewer moving parts.\n\n### How It Works\nTyro provides their own **Tyro App** or **Tyro SDK** that runs on the terminal or connects via their API. Your POS talks directly to Tyro\'s system instead of going through Linkly middleware.\n\n---\n\n### Step-by-Step (General Process)\n\n1. **Check if your POS supports it** — log into your POS backend or check their documentation for \"Tyro\" in the payment integrations list. Common POS systems with native Tyro support include:\n   - Lightspeed, Kounta/Lightspeed Restaurant, Square (limited), H&L, Impos, OrderMate, Bepoz, Redcat, and others\n\n2. **Enable Tyro in your POS settings**\n   - Go to your POS payment/integration settings\n   - Select **Tyro** as your EFTPOS provider (not Linkly/PC-EFTPOS)\n\n3. **Download the Tyro App** (if required)\n   - Some integrations need the **Tyro App** installed on the same machine or network — download it from [tyro.com](https://www.tyro.com)\n   - It runs in the background and handles communication with the terminal\n\n4. **Pair the terminal**\n   - Your POS will prompt you to enter a **pairing code**\n   - On the Tyro terminal, navigate to **Settings → POS Integration** and generate a pairing code\n   - Enter that code in your POS\n\n5. **Test a transaction**\n\n---\n\n### Advantages Over Linkly\n- One less piece of software to maintain\n- Tyro handles the integration updates directly\n- Generally more stable since there\'s no middleware layer\n- Easier setup\n\n---\n\n### If Your POS Doesn\'t Have Native Tyro Support\nYou\'d need to either:\n- Use **Linkly** as covered before, or\n- Contact your POS vendor — Tyro has a **partner program** and may have already built or be willing to build an integration\n\nTyro\'s developer docs are at **developer.tyro.com** if your POS vendor needs integration guidance.\n\nWhat POS system are you using? I can give more specific steps.',NULL,'extendedTextMessage',1778717213,'2026-05-14 00:06:53',NULL,NULL,NULL),
