(3677,'3EB016046AD52D5B2C627E','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Regan','231335629164614@lid','Regan',0,'Think of it like a really powerful, organised spreadsheet that lives on a server.\nYour app needs somewhere to store all its data — jobs, customers, invoices, technician locations, etc. Postgres is the software that stores all of that in structured tables (like spreadsheets), and lets your app ask questions like \"show me all overdue jobs in Adelaide\" and get fast, reliable answers.\nWhy not just use actual spreadsheets?\nSpreadsheets break down fast. They can\'t handle multiple people writing to them at the same time, they\'re slow with large data, and they have no security model. Postgres handles thousands of simultaneous users, keeps data consistent, and has been battle-tested for 30+ years.',NULL,'conversation',1778748097,'2026-05-14 08:41:37',NULL,NULL,NULL),
(3678,'3EB09CE7A800ED7241C818','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Regan','231335629164614@lid','Regan',0,'so probably worth it for me. it does have a free tier to start',NULL,'conversation',1778748182,'2026-05-14 08:43:02',NULL,NULL,NULL),
(3679,'3A0EE07E14FA17B766B1','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Curtis','61466848838:16@s.whatsapp.net','Me',1,'I was going to use neon for mine then brought it all into Orion instead',NULL,'conversation',1778749848,'2026-05-14 09:10:49',NULL,NULL,NULL),
(3680,'3EB030AE14513B41EC7F0D','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Dwayne Baird','144221143048242@lid','Dwayne Baird',0,'Forgebox has the power to pull and reference about 360,000 spreadsheet cells of data in the blink of an eye (less than half a second)\n\nSome cells can contain as much or even more information than the following:\n\"Large (Size) x1 @ 1.00; Full Cream - Lge (Milk) x1 @ 0.00; Extra Hot (Coffee Add-Ons) x1 @ 0.00; Caramel Syrup (Coffee Add-Ons) x1 @ 0.50; Sugar (Sugar) x1 @ 0.00\"\n\nIt does this from a modified version of mariadb with vectorisation included.\n\nI know there\'s reasons to use databricks, postgres and neon.. but you\'re not scaling and connecting databases across thousands of servers with autoscaling in the cloud.\nSo I can\'t recommend it, unless you love bringing a nuke to a knife fight.',NULL,'conversation',1778753028,'2026-05-14 10:03:48',NULL,NULL,NULL),
