INSERT INTO `browser_automation_runs` VALUES
(1,1,'manual','success',NULL,0,'Reading additional input from stdin...\nOpenAI Codex v0.122.0 (research preview)\n--------\nworkdir: /home/admin\nmodel: gpt-5.4\nprovider: openai\napproval: never\nsandbox: danger-full-access\nreasoning effort: high\nreasoning summaries: none\nsession id: 019db7bd-6ab2-7601-97a9-cd6e9088e692\n--------\nuser\nFirstly goto torn.com/gym.php and spend all my energy on training the Defense Skill. Then goto the crimes page, to cracking crimes and spend all my nerve on the bottom most cracking crime that is still in the state of brute force, once that has moved to \"crack\" move up the list until you get to the next brute force and use nerve on that and continue up the list until you have used all nerve.\ncodex\nI’m checking what browser automation is available locally and whether there’s an existing logged-in Torn session I can use. After that I’ll try to perform the gym and crimes actions directly.\nexec\n/bin/bash -lc \"ls -1 ~/.config | sed -n \'1,40p\'\" in /home/admin\n succeeded in 0ms:\nchromium\nclawhub\ncreate-next-app-nodejs\nnextjs-nodejs\nnotesmd-cli\nobsidian\nprocps\nsystemd\n\nexec\n/bin/bash -lc \'which chromium || which chromium-browser || which google-chrome || which google-chrome-stable || which firefox\' in /home/admin\n exited 1 in 0ms:\nexec\n/bin/bash -lc \'node -v && npm -v\' in /home/admin\n succeeded in 0ms:\nv24.14.0\n11.9.0\n\ncodex\nI found Node available and a Chromium config directory, but no browser binary in the default path from that first check. I’m locating the actual executable and then I’ll test whether the existing profile is logged into Torn.\nexec\n/bin/bash -lc \'command -v chromium; command -v chromium-browser; command -v google-chrome; command -v google-chrome-stable; command -v firefox\' in /home/admin\n exited 1 in 0ms:\nexec\n/bin/bash -lc \"ls -1 ~/.config/chromium | sed -n \'1,80p\'\" in /home/admin\n succeeded in 0ms:\nActorSafetyLists\nAmountExtractionHeuristicRegexes\nBrowserMetrics-spare