(34,'2a2ecbd2-7f8c-4cab-91fc-6501300ed4aa','user','text','I\'d like to know the process as to why some states in australia have the public holiday on 27th April instead of 25th of april','codex','gpt-5.4-mini',NULL,NULL,NULL,'{\"backend\":\"codex\"}','2026-04-26 11:01:41'),
(35,'2a2ecbd2-7f8c-4cab-91fc-6501300ed4aa','assistant','status','error: unexpected argument \'-s\' found\n\n  tip: to pass \'-s\' as a value, use \'-- -s\'\n\nUsage: codex exec resume [OPTIONS] [SESSION_ID] [PROMPT]\n\nFor more information, try \'--help\'.','codex','gpt-5.4-mini','error',NULL,NULL,'{\"backend\":\"codex\",\"status\":\"error\"}','2026-04-26 11:01:41'),
(36,'2a2ecbd2-7f8c-4cab-91fc-6501300ed4aa','user','text','I\'d like to know the process as to why some states in australia have the public holiday on 27th April instead of 25th of april','codex','gpt-5.4',NULL,NULL,NULL,'{\"backend\":\"codex\"}','2026-04-26 11:01:55'),
(37,'2a2ecbd2-7f8c-4cab-91fc-6501300ed4aa','assistant','text','This is because `ANZAC Day` is treated differently by each Australian state and territory.\n\nFor `2026`, `25 April` falls on a `Saturday`. In all states and territories, `Saturday 25 April 2026` is still ANZAC Day. The difference is that some jurisdictions also give an `additional public holiday` on `Monday 27 April 2026`, while others do not.\n\nThe process is basically this:\n\nEach state and territory sets its own public holiday rules by its own legislation or government declaration.\n`ANZAC Day` itself stays fixed on `25 April`.\nIf `25 April` lands on a weekend, some places create a substitute or additional Monday holiday so people still get a weekday day off.\nOther places keep the holiday only on the actual date, because they treat ANZAC Day as a fixed commemoration rather than a movable day off.\n\nFor `2026`, according to the Fair Work Ombudsman:\n`ACT`, `NSW`, and `WA` have both `Saturday 25 April` and `Monday 27 April` as public holidays.\n`NT`, `QLD`, `SA`, `TAS`, and `VIC` have only `Saturday 25 April` for ANZAC Day.\n\nNSW is a good example of the reasoning: the NSW government says `25 April` remains the day of commemoration, and the Monday holiday is an `additional` day, not a replacement.\n\nSources:\nFair Work Ombudsman: https://www.fairwork.gov.au/newsroom/news/anzac-day-public-holidays\nNSW Government: https://www.nsw.gov.au/about-nsw/anzac-day-nsw\nVictoria public holidays: https://business.vic.gov.au/business-information/public-holidays/victorian-public-holidays-2026\n\nIf you want, I can also give you a simple state-by-state table for `ANZAC Day 2026`.','codex','gpt-5.4',NULL,26839,781,'{\"thread_id\":\"019dc6e0-d2de-7330-af61-59b98a2d96c2\",\"cached_input_tokens\":6528,\"backend\":\"codex\"}','2026-04-26 11:02:20'),
(38,'2a2ecbd2-7f8c-4cab-91fc-6501300ed4aa','user','text','sure','codex','gpt-5.4-mini',NULL,NULL,NULL,'{\"backend\":\"codex\"}','2026-04-26 11:04:00'),
(39,'2a2ecbd2-7f8c-4cab-91fc-6501300ed4aa','assistant','text','Here’s the state-by-state view for `ANZAC Day 2026`:\n\n| Jurisdiction | `Saturday 25 April 2026` | `Monday 27 April 2026` | Notes |\n|---|---:|---:|---|\n| ACT | Yes | Yes | `27 April` is an additional public holiday |\n| NSW | Yes | Yes | `27 April` is an additional public holiday |\n| WA | Yes | Yes | `27 April` is an additional public holiday |\n| NT | Yes | No | Only `25 April` is the public holiday |\n| QLD | Yes | No | Only `25 April` is the public holiday |\n| SA | Yes | No | Only `25 April` is the public holiday |\n| TAS | Yes | No | Only `25 April` is the public holiday |\n| VIC | Yes | No | Only `25 April` is the public holiday |\n\nThe key point is that `25 April` is still ANZAC Day everywhere. In `ACT`, `NSW`, and `WA`, there is also an `additional public holiday` on `Monday 27 April 2026` because `25 April` falls on a Saturday.\n\nSources:\n- Fair Work Ombudsman: https://www.fairwork.gov.au/newsroom/news/anzac-day-public-holidays\n- Fair Work Ombudsman public holidays by state/territory: https://www.fairwork.gov.au/employment-conditions/public-holidays/2026-public-holidays\n\nIf you want, I can also turn this into a one-line explanation you can send to someone else.','codex','gpt-5.4-mini',NULL,26704,996,'{\"thread_id\":\"019dc6e2-b976-7c71-9986-cb616a2946fe\",\"cached_input_tokens\":18816,\"backend\":\"codex\"}','2026-04-26 11:04:17'),
(40,'d6c2f97e-f2bf-48c7-9182-79003c263b57','user','text','On the apps page can you build an app for me that replicates the original snake game? Make sure that if I’m loading on a mobile device it goes full screen and plays just like a modern version of the original snake game fully functioning.','codex','gpt-5.4-build',NULL,NULL,NULL,'{\"backend\":\"codex\"}','2026-04-26 11:14:14'),
(41,'d6c2f97e-f2bf-48c7-9182-79003c263b57','assistant','text','I can build it, but I can’t modify your project yet because this ForgeBox/Codex workspace is failing before any file command starts: `bwrap: loopback: Failed RTM_NEWADDR: Operation not permitted`.\n\nIf you want me to wire it directly into your apps page, send one of these:\n1. The path to the frontend app folder or the apps page file.\n2. A paste of the relevant app router/page component.\n3. A fixed workspace where shell/file access works.\n\nOnce I have access, I’ll add a fully playable Snake app with:\n- Classic gameplay updated for modern devices\n- Touch swipe controls plus keyboard controls\n- Mobile full-screen layout using the actual viewport height\n- Responsive canvas sizing\n- Start/restart, score, game over, food spawning, collision handling\n- Full-screen feel on phones with no scrolling or clipped UI\n\nIf you want, I can also give you a single self-contained React component right now that you can drop into the apps page manually.','codex','gpt-5.4-build',NULL,134401,1167,'{\"thread_id\":\"019dc6ec-194b-7af1-bfc2-d12d9328031d\",\"cached_input_tokens\":114944,\"backend\":\"codex\"}','2026-04-26 11:14:57'),
