(1253,'3EB0369B7D464E7E118A7D','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Dwayne Baird','144221143048242@lid','Dwayne Baird',0,'You\'re not dumb, the workflow is just unusual. Two steps.\n\nStep 1: keep talking to Claude on your phone, but ask it to write you a PRD (product requirements document) at the end. Tell it: \"Write me a PRD for this app covering what it does, who uses it, the features, and the user flows. Don\'t pick a tech stack, don\'t design the database, don\'t choose a framework. Just describe what the app needs to do.\"\n\nStep 2: when you\'re at the PC, paste that PRD into the ForgeBox App Builder window. ForgeBox already knows what it is, what\'s installed, what runs efficiently on it, and how everything fits together. It reads your PRD and decides Node vs PHP vs Python, what database tables, what services, all of it.\nThe split is: phone Claude handles the what. ForgeBox handles the how.\n\nDon\'t tell phone Claude \"use Node\" or \"use Python.\" That\'s ForgeBox\'s job. If you lock in a stack now, ForgeBox has to either argue with you or build something less efficient than it would have chosen.',NULL,'conversation',1777120338,'2026-04-25 12:32:18',NULL,NULL,NULL),
