(1623,'3EB0ACB6A6B6C07F9579BE','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Dwayne Baird','144221143048242@lid','Dwayne Baird',0,'For React, it\'s the same as Node.js only a framework for build and deploy:\nYou could just increase the swap file to ~16GB which will be a big bottle neck for slow building of React apps.\n\nOr go for an 8 GB ForgeBox; its plenty for a self-contained website host that also builds React projects. After current services (~2.4 GB) you\'d have ~5 GB free, comfortable for any Vite build and most Next.js production builds. \nMainstream React projects don\'t peak above 3 GB.',NULL,'conversation',1777342927,'2026-04-28 02:22:08',NULL,NULL,NULL),
(1624,'3EB0115802DCF05A5FD96C','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Curtis','61466848838:16@s.whatsapp.net','Me',1,'MMM good to know',NULL,'conversation',1777342975,'2026-04-28 02:22:56',NULL,NULL,NULL),
(1625,'3EB0BF7E437C60F87805F6','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Dwayne Baird','144221143048242@lid','Dwayne Baird',0,'Lets be honest, if you\'re porting a production build for a large SaaS codebase onto the ForgeBox, get 8GB, or if we\'re talking a massive production SaaS platform (like netflix or something...) go with 16GB',NULL,'conversation',1777343344,'2026-04-28 02:29:04',NULL,NULL,NULL),
(1626,'3EB0CC714E165187164AD4','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Dwayne Baird','144221143048242@lid','Dwayne Baird',0,'If you\'re a backyard SaaS run from grandma\'s basement suck up the 50-240 second extra build time because it\'s hammering the swap file.',NULL,'conversation',1777343416,'2026-04-28 02:30:17',NULL,NULL,NULL),
