(1960,'ACE4CAEC6FA814CBC91D18E1A94E3FA9','61419807085-1517197220@g.us',NULL,'Chas Hilder','183519825383666@lid','Chas Hilder',0,'Q&A Sessions Across All Assemblies to answer questions about the changes of Rule of Association.\r\n\r\nDear Area Leaders and House Leaders,\r\n\r\nJust to keep you in the Loop! In preparation of the General meeting on May 16th.\n\nThe pastors met this week and have agreed that we will expand the efforts to inform and consult with our people in the lead up to the general meeting currently planned for the 16th of May. We will apologise to the saints for any confusion that may have been caused with last Sundays announcement.\n\r\nWe have arranged a series of Question & Answer sessions across all assemblies over the next 2 weeks. (schedule of 1st week attached)\r\n\r\nThese sessions are designed to:\r\n\r\n•⁠  ⁠Help the saints better understand the proposed changes\r\n•⁠  ⁠Provide clarity in an open discussion\r\n•⁠  ⁠Give everyone the opportunity to ask questions and be heard\r\n\r\nTo ensure that everyone feels comfortable participating, we will also be sharing a QR code (attached on a separate slide). This will allow the saints to submit questions anonymously, which will then be addressed by the moderator during the sessions as time allows.\r\n\r\nWe encourage you to:\r\n\r\n•⁠  ⁠Promote these sessions within your areas and house meetings\r\n•⁠  ⁠Encourage participation, both in person and through submitted questions\r\n\nIf some are concerned and need a visit we will be happy to visit.\r\n\r\nWe look forward to hearing the voices of the saints.\r\n\n\r\nWe will follow up with 2 slides and a message to distribute to your areas.',NULL,'extendedTextMessage',1777677808,'2026-05-01 23:23:28',NULL,NULL,NULL),
