(4457,'3EB0A3F2696BB4231CFB16','144221143048242@lid',NULL,'Dwayne Baird','144221143048242@lid','Dwayne Baird',0,'Pegging the insurance limits properly requires someone who can speak to the architecture. Now you\'ll be my proxy in that room.\n\nA quick architectural summary so Rob can peg the limits against the actual data profile rather than a generic software vendor template. Feel free to forward, paraphrase, or read any of this in the room.\n\nWhat sits in the DataForge platform:\n- Assessment scores (DQ, AQ, IQ, EQ), leadership strength calculations, ambition ratings and succession planning notes\n- Data is attached to pseudonymous indices, not employee names or identifiers\n- Single tenancy in AWS Sydney, no subprocessors other than AWS\n- Assessment inputs are processed client-side in the browser before submission\n\nWhat does NOT sit in the DataForge platform:\n- No employee names, contact details or other PII at rest\n- No payment card data, health data, financial data or government IDs\n- No production data during the MVP development period\n- Identity resolution between the pseudonymous indices and named employees occurs in News Corp\'s Workday environment via API\n\nWhy this matters for pegging the limit:\n- A breach of the DataForge platform in isolation yields opinion-based scores attached to opaque tokens\n- Re-identification requires access to Workday, which News Corp controls\n- Under the OAIC Notifiable Data Breach framework, the \'likely risk of serious harm to an identifiable individual\' trigger is materially reduced where re-identification keys are held by the controller rather than the processor\n- Forensic and notification costs, the dominant cost drivers in cyber claims, are reduced by this architecture\n\nContract context:\n- MVP build fee AUD 85,000, ongoing SaaS at AUD 30 per month for the News Corp group\n- Non-operational HR planning tool, not a business-critical workload\n- Contractual liability and indemnity caps already in place under the MSA',NULL,'extendedTextMessage',1779173789,'2026-05-19 06:56:30',NULL,NULL,NULL),
