(4519,'3EB02CBD5C5C1D7933617D','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Dwayne Baird','144221143048242@lid','Dwayne Baird',0,'Send this as well, even if it\'s still working though:\nAmendment to the mDNS/hostname audit task — also cover the avahi \"rename storm\"\n\n  The original brief omitted a third failure mode. Keep everything you\'re already doing and add the following.\n\n  Extra background — two rename-storm variants\n\n  - Watchdog loop: if a machine\'s kernel hostname was changed away from forgebox (a manual rename, or a systemd override forcing the box name after onboarding), the watchdog can no longer resolve forgebox.local locally (watchdog.sh:22,66-67), sets need_restart_avahi=1, and\n  restarts avahi (:74) every tick (~90 s). Unlike the IPv6 collision, this is visible in that box\'s own avahi logs as a steady restart cadence.\n  - daemon-reload churn: a setup/NetworkManager path calling systemctl daemon-reload repeatedly restarts avahi as a dependent unit — much higher and burstier restart counts than the ~90 s watchdog cadence (historically hundreds overnight).\n\n  Context: /opt/forgebox/docs/runbook-mdns-hostname-conflicts.md.\n\n  Additional commands to collect per machine\n\n  grep -E \'127.0.1.1\' /etc/hosts                               # must contain the forgebox token\n  systemctl list-unit-files | grep -i hostname                 # any override forcing a non-forgebox hostname\n  journalctl -u avahi-daemon --since \"-24h\" | grep -c \"starting up\"\n  journalctl --since \"-24h\" | grep -c \"Reloading.*daemon\\|daemon-reload\"\n\n  Additional pass criteria (PASS/FAIL per machine)\n\n  - Kernel hostname is forgebox; if not, identify what set it (manual rename vs systemd override).\n  - /etc/hosts 127.0.1.1 still contains the forgebox token.\n  - avahi restarts in the last 24 h are low (single digits). If elevated, classify: steady ~90 s cadence = watchdog/hostname loop; high irregular bursts correlating with daemon-reload events = reload churn.\n\n  Add to the deliverable\n\n  For every elevated-restart machine, state the storm class (watchdog rename loop vs daemon-reload churn vs the IPv6-collision external flap), the trigger you found, and the runbook section to apply. Still read-only — apply nothing.',NULL,'conversation',1779185972,'2026-05-19 10:19:33',NULL,NULL,NULL),
