(4526,'3EB0EE3752B416BD440626','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Dwayne Baird','144221143048242@lid','Dwayne Baird',0,'Stop it and send this:\nAmendment 2 — concrete targets and collision pair\n\n  The machines in scope are specifically orion.local and chuck.local — two clones co-located on the client\'s LAN. toby is not necessarily on that network, so do not treat this as \"clones vs toby.\" Treat orion and chuck as the colliding pair: the IPv6 link-local cross-machine\n  comparison is between orion.local and chuck.local themselves, and uniqueness (regenerated IPv6 link-local stable-secret + unique avahi host-name=) must be enforced between those two.\n\n  Run the full audit (original brief + the rename-storm amendment) against both orion.local and chuck.local. In the deliverable, explicitly state whether their fe80:: link-local addresses collide with each other, and whether each one\'s avahi host-name= is distinct (orion vs\n  chuck). If either host is unreachable, report that rather than assuming it is off — do not apply fixes.',NULL,'conversation',1779186130,'2026-05-19 10:22:10',NULL,NULL,NULL),
