(4546,'3EB084CF9AD6D51B2ED851','120363346032343642@g.us',NULL,'Dwayne Baird','144221143048242@lid','Dwayne Baird',0,'Task: fix the avahi watchdog rename-loop on THIS box (local, validated, with rollback)\n\n  You are operating in a local SSH session on a single ForgeBox clone. Apply the fix to this box only, using paramiko sudo Forgebox3.b for privileged steps, you have auth. Do not connect to any other machine.\n\n  Root cause: /opt/forgebox/onboarding/bin/watchdog.sh:22 hard-codes the mDNS health probe to forgebox.local. This box was deliberately renamed (kernel hostname is not forgebox), so that probe never resolves locally, the check at :66 fails every watchdog tick, and avahi is\n  restarted (:73) every ~60–90 s. The fix makes the probe track this box\'s real hostname. The rename is intentional — do not revert the kernel hostname, do not change any onboarding env var, and do not modify anything else under /opt/forgebox/onboarding/.\n\n  Safety gates — if any fails, change nothing and report why:\n\n  1. test \"$(hostname)\" != forgebox — if the kernel hostname IS forgebox, this box is not a renamed clone; abort (the existing probe is already correct here).\n  2. getent hosts \"$(hostname).local\" must return an address — if $(hostname).local does not resolve locally, abort and report (the fix would not help and indicates a deeper avahi problem).\n  3. Line 22 of /opt/forgebox/onboarding/bin/watchdog.sh must be exactly:\n  MDNS_NAME=\"${FORGEBOX_ONBOARDING_HOSTNAME:-forgebox}.local\"\n  If it is anything else (already patched, or different content), abort and report the actual line — do not edit.\n\n  Apply (only if all gates pass):\n\n  1. Back up the file (sudo, preserve mode): copy to watchdog.sh.bak.<UTC-timestamp> in the same directory.\n  2. Replace line 22 exactly:\n    - from: MDNS_NAME=\"${FORGEBOX_ONBOARDING_HOSTNAME:-forgebox}.local\"\n    - to:   MDNS_NAME=\"$(hostname).local\"\n  (Literal — the script evaluates $(hostname) at runtime. Change nothing else.)\n\n  Validate:\n\n  1. bash -n /opt/forgebox/onboarding/bin/watchdog.sh — syntax must pass.\n  2. Run the watchdog as it actually runs, in dry-run, with sudo: /opt/forgebox/onboarding/bin/watchdog.sh --dry-run — confirm it does not report restarting avahi for the mDNS reason.\n  3. Restart count check: journalctl -u avahi-daemon --since \"-15min\" | grep -c \"starting up\", wait ~4 minutes, re-run — confirm the count has stopped climbing.\n\n  Rollback: if syntax fails, dry-run still flags an avahi restart, or restarts keep climbing — restore the timestamped backup, verify restored, and report FAIL.\n\n  Report back: this box\'s hostname; the old and new line 22; backup path; syntax result; dry-run result; avahi restart count before and ~4 min after; and PASS / FAIL / ABORTED-with-reason. Make no other changes.',NULL,'conversation',1779187216,'2026-05-19 10:40:16',NULL,NULL,NULL),
