(4878,'3EB085B95B27763660F35D','120363400908812783@g.us',NULL,'Curtis','61466848838:16@s.whatsapp.net','Me',1,'Comparing 1.081 with 1.08, 1.06 and the initial docs from October last year (HLA, Scope and Agreement). I\'m not fighting anything here just want 1.081 to have a consistent message. I\'ve got to head into a meeting but i\'l leave the AI summery here for you and chat about it when i come out. \n\nDoes the earlier pricing match 1.081?\nNo — and there are several mismatches and gaps:\n\n1.081 has no MVP build fee at all. The trajectory is: Scope had a real range → non-SaaS Agreement firmed it at AUD 85k → SaaS 1.06/1.08 reduced this to a vague placeholder pointing at a non-existent \"commercial section\" → 1.081 deleted even the placeholder. There is no dollar figure in any signable SaaS version.\n\nScope vs non-SaaS Agreement (1) don\'t fully reconcile either:\n\nScope phases sum to $65k build + $10k contingency = $75k (the top of the Scope range).\nThe non-SaaS Agreement says $75k build + $10k contingency = $85k total.\nSo the contingency appears to have been counted twice when moving from Scope to Agreement (1), or the build was uplifted by $10k without explanation. Either way the $85k total in Agreement (1) is $10k above the top of the Scope estimate.\nNon-SaaS Agreement (1) vs SaaS 1.06/1.08/1.081 — pricing model fundamentally changed:\n\nAgreement (1) is for internal deployment at News Corp (source code delivered, perpetual licence, no SaaS hosting). Out-of-scope explicitly lists \"Any SaaS hosting or services\" and \"third-party licence fees.\"\nSaaS 1.06–1.081 is the opposite: DataForge owns the IP, hosts on AWS, News Corp gets free SaaS access. So Agreement (1)\'s AUD 85k is for a different commercial deal — not directly transferable as the MVP fee in 1.081.\nBut nothing in 1.081 explicitly says the AUD 85k Agreement (1) figure has been superseded, retained, or revised. If both documents are circulating, this is ambiguous.\nNon-refundable deposit clause lost in transition. Agreement (1) explicitly says the 50% deposit is non-refundable. SaaS 1.06/1.08/1.081 Schedule 4 just says \"Deposit of fifty percent payable on signature to commence work\" — refundability is silent.\n\nTermination-for-convenience payment terms lost. Agreement (1) §10 said the client pays for work performed + reasonable committed costs on convenience termination. SaaS 1.06/1.08/1.081 §19.3 simply lets the client terminate on 30 days\' notice with no payment-on-termination obligation — a meaningful commercial swing in News Corp\'s favour, but it leaves DataForge exposed mid-build if the MVP fee isn\'t fully prepaid.\n\n\nBottom line\nThe only earlier doc with a hard total contract price is Talent & Succession Agreement (1).docx: AUD 85,000 (AUD 75k build + AUD 10k contingency), but it\'s for the non-SaaS / internal-deployment model.\nThe Scope doc has phase-level estimates ($65k–$75k + $10k contingency) that don\'t cleanly reconcile with that AUD 85k figure.\nNone of the SaaS versions (1.06, 1.08, 1.081) state a build fee at all — the trajectory is placeholder → blank.\nIf the intent is for 1.081 to carry over the AUD 85k from Agreement (1), that needs to be explicitly inserted into Schedule 4 (and the contingency/non-refundable-deposit/termination-payment language needs to come with it).',NULL,'conversation',1779321720,'2026-05-21 00:02:00',NULL,NULL,NULL),
